         <abstract>
            <p>A consistent and adequate policy of in-lieu tax payments is needed. Lack of such a policy has brought embarrassment to many local units. Important opinion believes that the courts might rule that government property used for business purposes need not be tax-exempt. It might be reasonable for the government to pay taxes on camp sites. Payment of minimum in-lieu taxes on a fixed basis pending maturing of timber in national forests is needed. The formula for TVA payments works a gross inequity against North Carolina.</p>
